93
00:05:28,373 --> 00:05:31,693
So there's a lot of effort under way--
at least within the UN system--

94
00:05:31,693 --> 00:05:35,935
to make the process,
to integrate that as much as possible.

95
00:05:35,935 --> 00:05:41,934
If I look at Sendai, I would have to say
that if there is one

96
00:05:41,934 --> 00:05:46,455
fundamental risk treatment
to reduce disaster risk

97
00:05:46,455 --> 00:05:50,317
it is to reduce greenhouse gases
as quickly as possible.

98
00:05:50,317 --> 00:05:55,776
Just because climate change 
will have such an existential impact

99
00:05:55,776 --> 00:05:58,404
on everything else, even conflict.

100
00:05:58,404 --> 00:06:03,757
We've seen in the case of the Middle East,
an unprecedented period of drought,

101
00:06:03,757 --> 00:06:07,273
which of course you can't necessarily link
any one event to climate change,

102
00:06:07,273 --> 00:06:09,940
but it's what you'd expect 
from climate change.

103
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:14,367
It triggered a mass migration of hundreds 
of thousands of people into cities.

104
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:16,179
It wasn't the cause of the Syrian crisis,

105
00:06:16,179 --> 00:06:19,686
but it was certainly 
a contributing cause of even conflict.

106
00:06:19,686 --> 00:06:23,990
So for me, that absolutely 
has to be integrated

107
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:26,611
and so when we talk 
about disaster risk reduction,

108
00:06:26,611 --> 00:06:28,171
we're very much talking about

109
00:06:28,171 --> 00:06:31,139
climate change mitigation
as a risk treatment,

110
00:06:31,139 --> 00:06:33,632
and mitigation, 
addressing loss and damage,

111
00:06:33,632 --> 00:06:36,000
adaptation to climate change.

112
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:41,582
And all of those have fundamental science
and technology issues associated with them.

113
00:06:41,582 --> 00:06:45,183
What are your key messages to researchers
on science and technology for DRR?

114
00:06:45,183 --> 00:06:48,805
The first message 
is that what they're doing,

115
00:06:48,805 --> 00:06:53,464
the development of science and technology
on this issue is <i>really</i> important

116
00:06:53,464 --> 00:06:57,512
and urgent because when we talk 
about disaster risk,

117
00:06:57,512 --> 00:07:00,313
it's a nice, cold-sounding term,

118
00:07:00,313 --> 00:07:03,804
but it means hundreds
of thousands of deaths.

119
00:07:03,804 --> 00:07:06,814
It means increases in poverty.

120
00:07:06,814 --> 00:07:10,104
It means huge economic losses.

121
00:07:10,104 --> 00:07:14,356
Over 350 billion a year,
which is money that could be spent

122
00:07:14,356 --> 00:07:19,025
on teaching and medicines,
and economic development.

123
00:07:19,685 --> 00:07:22,436
The second message is that

124
00:07:22,436 --> 00:07:26,506
this is not an issue 
that you solve in a silo.

125
00:07:27,576 --> 00:07:33,048
Disaster risk, it's multi-hazard risk
and it's social science,

126
00:07:33,048 --> 00:07:36,857
it's physical sci-- 
it's physicists, it's geologists,

127
00:07:36,857 --> 00:07:41,170
it's psychologists, 
it's political scientists.

128
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:44,099
The only solutions that are going to work

129
00:07:44,939 --> 00:07:48,129
are going to be multidisciplinary,
interdisciplinary.

130
00:07:48,129 --> 00:07:52,701
I was in California-- I'm Australian
but was in California recently--

131
00:07:53,201 --> 00:07:56,211
northern California 
having lunch in a restaurant,

132
00:07:56,211 --> 00:07:58,992
and suddenly all the cell phones 
went off at once.

133
00:07:58,992 --> 00:08:01,763
And when we looked, 
everyone stopped and read their phone.

134
00:08:01,763 --> 00:08:06,461
My phone said, "Tornado heading your way.
Take cover immediately."

135
00:08:06,941 --> 00:08:08,572
And there was a lot of talking

136
00:08:08,572 --> 00:08:11,311
and then everyone 
just went back to eating.

137
00:08:11,311 --> 00:08:14,228
I got up and went outside and looked,
and I could see the cloud was moving

138
00:08:14,228 --> 00:08:16,763
in the other direction,
the storm cloud.

139
00:08:16,763 --> 00:08:18,764
But the reason everyone ignored that

140
00:08:18,764 --> 00:08:23,192
was because there had never been a tornado
in that place before,

141
00:08:23,192 --> 00:08:27,493
at least in people's memories,
so they just assumed it must be a mistake.

142
00:08:27,493 --> 00:08:31,600
In this case, it was okay, 
but the lesson they learned was

143
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:36,834
number one, you can ignore warning
even of the highest technology,

144
00:08:36,834 --> 00:08:39,966
the most efficient sort of warning 
you could imagine;

145
00:08:39,966 --> 00:08:43,976
and number two, probably next time
they'll do the same thing,

146
00:08:43,976 --> 00:08:45,836
and next time they mightn't be lucky.

147
00:08:45,836 --> 00:08:49,357
So it just highlighted for me
that that element of the psychology,

148
00:08:49,357 --> 00:08:51,928
and the training and the awareness raising

149
00:08:51,928 --> 00:08:54,839
has to go hand in hand with technologies

150
00:08:54,839 --> 00:08:59,199
and other solutions
involving technology and science,

151
00:08:59,199 --> 00:09:00,478
in order for it to be effective.

152
00:09:00,478 --> 00:09:02,705
And if one is missing 
then you might as well

153
00:09:02,705 --> 00:09:05,176
not even have the other
because it won't work.

